Dielectric loss behavior is high association with the electrical conductivity (σ) of the Ni@C absorber, which plays a key role to affect the storage and loss ability toward the electromagnetic wave energy. According to the Debye theory, the relationship between the complex permittivity (ε′, ε″) and intrinsic conductivity (σ) can be explained as follows: [54, 55]:3ε′=ε∞+εs-ε∞1+ωτ2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
